Northern Telecomsaid it shipped the first digital central office switchingsystem it sold to Nippon Telegraph and Telephone under theterms of a 250 mln dlrs supply agreement.    The agreement began with the signing of a letter ofunderstanding in December 1985. THe formal seven-year agreementwas signed in May 1986.    The Northern Telecom systems is the first U.S.-manufactureddigital central office switching systems to be installed in theJapanese public telephone network, it said.   Reuter&#3;